          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAANL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Argonne 60 in. cyclotron."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Targets of U-233, U-235, U-238 and Np-237. Usually",
                "uranium metal foils about 0.002 in. thick were used",
                "as targets. They were covered with pure Al foils",
                "which acted as catcher foils for the fission",
                "products. In most experiments only the catcher foils",
                "were used for preparing the samples, enabling",
                "repeated use of the valuable fissionable foils. By",
                "bombarding a blank aluminum foil alone it was shown",
                "that no disturbing activity was produced in the",
                "catcher foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two 3 in. x 3 in. NaI(T1) crystals."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "ACTIV",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The chemical separation of cesium",
                "was done essentially by two consecutive ironhydroxide",
                "precipitations preceded and followed by",
                "precipitations of cesium as cesium-perchlorate.",
                "Initially, the gamma-spectrum was measured with a 3",
                "in. by 3 in. NaI(T1) crystal with conventional",
                "electronics and a 200-channel pulse height analyzer.",
                "Aluminum absorbers of appropriate thickness",
                "prevented beta-particles from entering the crystal.",
                "At a later stage of the work, Compton anticoincidence",
                "counting equipment became available. Two 4 in. x 4",
                "in. NaI(TI) crystals facing each other and having the",
                "sample between them were surrounded by a large",
                "plastic scintillator. Moreover any gamma-ray which is",
                "in coincidence with another one was counted with",
                "reduced efficiency since the second gamma ray in the",
                "cascade could also produce anticoincidence pulses in",
                "the surrounding plastic scintillator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A correction was applied for gamma-absorption in the",
                "aluminum beta-absorbers."
              ]
            }
          ],
